Description:
A cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in tawk.to allows a remote attacker (user) to inject arbitrary Javascript or HTML by uploading a pdf file containing malicious code, which would result in XSS being stored in its server files.

Vulnerability Type: Stored XSS

Attack Vectors:

  1.Construct pdf files containing malicious code: javascript:app.alert(1);
  2.Upload a pdf file containing XSS malicious code on the chat page: https://tawk.to/chat/*
  
Now when someone accesses the malicious file(The uploaded file address can be easily obtained), alert(1) will be executed.
